# Skill: Responsive UX and Motion

Use this skill when implementing layout breakpoints, mobile UX, sticky behavior, scroll effects, transitions, overlays, and animations.

## Responsive Rules
- Treat mobile UX as first-class, not an afterthought.
- Prevent horizontal overflow at all breakpoints.
- Use the existing container/gutter tokens where possible.
- Use responsive breakpoints around:
  - 1200px
  - 991px
  - 768px
  - 575px
- Desktop should use an editorial grid with sidebar.
- Tablet should use simplified two-column layouts.
- Mobile should use stacked cards, compact header, horizontal category nav, and drawer menu.
- Bangla headlines need comfortable line-height and size on mobile.

## Motion Rules
- Keep motion subtle, premium, and fast.
- Use CSS transitions for hover/focus states.
- Use `IntersectionObserver` for scroll reveal.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- Avoid animations that cause layout shift.
- Do not animate too many heavy properties.
- Prefer opacity and transform animations.

## Required Interactions
- Sticky header style change on scroll.
- Search overlay open/close.
- Mobile drawer open/close.
- Back-to-top button visibility on scroll.
- Scroll reveal for cards/sections.
- Card hover lift and image zoom.
- Ticker pause on hover.

## Acceptance Checklist
- Works on desktop, tablet, and mobile.
- No layout overflow.
- Motion is professional and not distracting.
- Reduced-motion users are respected.
- Overlay and drawer interactions feel smooth.
